            <title>Ralph Rio comments on current trends for CMMS/EAM systems</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span&gt;Save Money with Better Asset Management: In this video, Ralph Rio is interviewed at the ARC World Industry Forum Orlando 2010 by &lt;em&gt;Supply Chain Brain &lt;/em&gt;magazine on the current trends for EAM systems from a recent survey.&lt;br /&gt;
	&lt;br /&gt;
	Enterprise asset management (EAM) systems are used to manage the maintenance of equipment and facilities in large industrial, commercial or healthcare sites. Computerize maintenance management systems (CMMS) is another term commonly used for this type of application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
