                <a10:name>RP news wires</a10:name>
            </a10:author>
            <category>Industry News</category>
            <category>Articles</category>
            <title>Ivara and MRO Software announce partnership</title>
            <description>&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;&lt;SPAN lang=EN style="mso-ansi-language: EN"&gt;MRO Software Inc., a leading provider of asset and service management solutions, and &lt;/SPAN&gt;Ivara Corporation, an industry leader and innovator in asset reliability solutions, announced July 25 that Ivara has joined the MRO Software Complementary Solution Partner program.&amp;nbsp; &lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;Ivara is an industry leader in equipment reliability consulting services and enabling technologies and the parent company of Aladon LLC, specialists in the facilitation and training of Reliability-Centered Maintenance methodologies. As a reliability partner for MRO Software, Ivara will deliver enhanced reliability capabilities to complement the Maximo Enterprise Suite. The combined offering supported by Ivaras reliability software, EXP, will help customers to improve the effectiveness of their maintenance organization and overall equipment performance. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;We conducted a survey to better understand our customers equipment reliability needs, says Johan Arts, vice president, Industry and Solutions Marketing,&amp;nbsp;MRO Software. Clearly, equipment reliability is extremely important to our customers in many industries, including, utilities, oil and gas, manufacturing, and transportation. We found more than 70 percent of respondents reliability programs are supported by internally developed applications, and over 85 percent of respondents indicate a direct tie between reliability programs and improved equipment performance. As of result of this feedback, we are pleased to establish a partnership with Ivara.&amp;nbsp;Their technology and reliability expertise meets our customers need for additional reliability support and leverages the functionality of our Maximo Enterprise Suite.&amp;nbsp; &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"&gt;For executives&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT face=Arial&gt;&lt;B&gt;,&lt;/B&gt; increased asset reliability translates directly into a big improvement to the bottom line. The integrated Ivara-MRO Software offering delivers a complete reliability system that optimizes both equipment and financial performance, says Gerry Bleau, chief executive officer, Ivara Corporation.&amp;nbsp; We are pleased to join with MRO Software and look forward to &lt;SPAN lang=EN-CA style="mso-ansi-language: EN-CA"&gt;supporting customers in their journey toward optimized reliability.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/CMMS_and_EAM/~4/HpwHW_tw3sE" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2006-07-26T00:00:00-05:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/2129/ivara-mro-software-announce-partnership" />
        <feedburner:origLink>http://reliableplant.com/Read/2129/ivara-mro-software-announce-partnership</feedburner:origLink></item>
        <item>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:noria.com,2010-06-10:publishing:magazines:rp:c67b3f99-321f-474a-902d-9cf800d9f914</guid>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/CMMS_and_EAM/~3/loSSOKhqXjw/cmms</link>
            <a10:author>
                <a10:name>Paul V. Arnold</a10:name>
            </a10:author>
            <category>Magazine Articles</category>
            <category>Articles</category>
            <title>Few make the most of their CMMS</title>
            <description>&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;A whopping 94.7 percent of plant maintenance managers feel they are not using their computerized maintenance management software system to its maximum capability, according to the results of a national CMMS survey conducted for &lt;i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;Reliable Plant&lt;/i&gt; magazine by educator, consultant and author Kris Bagadia.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;I knew that it was going to be a high percentage. I didn&amp;rsquo;t know it was going to be that high,&amp;rdquo; says Bagadia, whose extensive survey was completed this past winter by 299 industrial maintenance professionals. &amp;ldquo;I have estimated for years that 80 percent of installations fail. The data in this survey works to confirm that high failure rate.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;Besides providing the results to &lt;i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"&gt;Reliable Plant&lt;/i&gt;, Bagadia is using the new data as the focus of his book &amp;ldquo;CMMS Made Simple&amp;rdquo;, which will be published this summer by McGraw-Hill. &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Through this project, I wanted maintenance leaders to take a look in the mirror &amp;ndash; look at their system, what they are doing and what they want it to do,&amp;rdquo; he says. &amp;ldquo;More often than not, they will find that the CMMS has the capability to do what they need it to do; it&amp;rsquo;s just not being used in that manner. They don&amp;rsquo;t have to make another investment. What they need is the time, training and resources to do more with what they have. In some cases, though, they will find that they made a wrong selection, and it&amp;rsquo;s time to admit it and fix it.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;The survey respondents, on average:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;bull; work at a facility with 350 employees&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;bull; manage a maintenance staff of 15 employees&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;bull; oversee the maintenance of 938 plant assets&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;bull; employ CMMS systems that track 2,500 spare parts, and issue 100 work orders and 25 purchase orders per week&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;Obstacles to hurdle&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;The fact that maintenance departments struggle to get the most out of their CMMS systems shouldn&amp;rsquo;t be a surprise. A host of studies on this subject have been conducted over the past decade. But, 94.7 percent? That&amp;rsquo;s a figure that displays the full extent of the problem. It also shows that little progress has been made over the past decade to solve maintenance&amp;rsquo;s challenges, confusion and frustration in this area.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;Comments on the survey forms frankly list a myriad of factors that explain CMMS suboptimization:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;The program being used is way too complicated.&amp;rdquo; (That&amp;rsquo;s not surprising since nearly three out of 10 survey respondents said it took between one year and three years to implement their CMMS system.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We aren&amp;rsquo;t using the data to make decisions. The CMMS is more of an automated record keeper than an analysis tool.&amp;rdquo; &lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;There are more modules than we have the capacity to use.&amp;rdquo; (CMMS modules used by respondents are: preventive maintenance, 86.4 percent; work order, 83.5 percent; equipment, 78 percent; inventory, 43.2 percent; and purchase order, 29.7 percent).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It&amp;rsquo;s an old system that needs an upgrade.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;The software has limitations.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It would take precious hours. It&amp;rsquo;s not just hours sitting at a machine, but training time to learn about the program so that new information can be used effectively.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It has modules &amp;ndash; parts inventory, POs, etc. &amp;ndash; that aren&amp;rsquo;t currently being used. The reason is the time and data collection needed to load the module.&amp;rdquo; (More than one in four respondents said it took between 100 and 200 hours of maintenance employees&amp;rsquo; time to collect data for CMMS implementation; nearly one in four said it took more than 500 hours).&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Our maintenance technicians are not computer literate.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;It poorly interfaces with the accounting and SAP software. That leads to double entry of all POs.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;There&amp;rsquo;s a lack of expertise to learn and maintain the system, and a lack of clerical help for inputting the data. The data has more capabilities, but we don&amp;rsquo;t have enough resources to utilize them.&amp;rdquo; (Three out of five respondents use clerical support to enter data; on average, this support enters data 20 hours per week.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;The products we have used are far too cumbersome and complex for our needs.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We must apply our limited resources to putting out fires.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;We receive little support from our information technology group.&amp;rdquo; (A total of 32.9 percent of respondents said MIS/IT doesn&amp;rsquo;t give the system a high priority.)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;The bottom line?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;With feedback such as this, is it any wonder that the survey respondents point to less-than-stellar returns from their CMMS investment?&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;When asked what percent of their total maintenance budget has been saved as a result of better scheduling through their CMMS, nearly three out of 10 respondents said &amp;ldquo;5 or less percent.&amp;rdquo; Savings as a result of increased spare parts availability? Four out or 10 said &amp;ldquo;5 or less percent.&amp;rdquo; Savings as a result of increased machine availability? One in three said &amp;ldquo;5 or less percent.&amp;rdquo; Savings as a result of better inventory control? Again, one in three said &amp;ldquo;5 or less percent.&amp;rdquo; These return-on-investment results just might explain why only 77.5 percent of respondents said that their upper management is committed to the maintenance department&amp;rsquo;s CMMS program.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;A CMMS, used properly, can help you do more, do it more efficiently, and do it with less,&amp;rdquo; says Bagadia. &amp;ldquo;Most maintenance departments, though, aren&amp;rsquo;t realizing all of the gains. To turn the tide, it&amp;rsquo;s going to take some serious commitment on somebody&amp;rsquo;s part. Maintenance has to be committed to this as an improvement tool. MIS&amp;rsquo;s lack of involvement and support? That has to change. Part of it also lies with upper management. Unless they are committed to this and unless they take maintenance seriously, it will not change. They give maintenance the software, but they won&amp;rsquo;t provide the $5,000 or $10,000 for training. All those factors added together could well explain why maintenance only uses the system to submit work orders.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;Bagadia believes a system audit is a necessary first step to improvement.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;Either by yourself or through an outside firm, you need do an annual audit,&amp;rdquo; he says. &amp;ldquo;You need to see what the system is doing. Is it doing what&amp;rsquo;s expected, or can it do more?&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;The future&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;The survey showed that only around one in four respondents currently use imaging options in the CMMS to attach CAD drawings, digital photos or scanned images to records. Just one in four use handheld devices (PDAs, bar code scanners, etc.) in conjunction with the system. Bagadia sees great potential in such applications.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&amp;ldquo;I think these are areas of huge, huge opportunity for improvement,&amp;rdquo; he says. &amp;ldquo;That is where everybody has to go. This is relatively untapped. We should be talking more about these types of applications. These can really increase your efficiency and productivity.&amp;rdquo;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;
	&lt;span style="font-family: arial; color: black; font-size: 10pt"&gt;To view the full report, which breaks down data for all 39 survey questions, contact Kris Bagadia at krisb@peakis.com or 262-783-6260.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/CMMS_and_EAM/~4/loSSOKhqXjw" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2006-05-31T00:00:00-05:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/1627/cmms" />
